entry.sense:
SaboSabN, (M, Ḳ,) applied to a camel, (M,) Thick, or big, and strong; 
as also SubaASibN↓, (M, Ḳ, TA, in the CK SabaASib,) so applied; (M;) 
and SaboSaAbN↓, (Ḳ,) likewise so applied. (TA.)

hom.sense:
SuboHapN The early part of the forenoon, after sunrise; syn. DuHFI; 
as also SaboHapN↓: (Mṣb:) or the period of one's entering upon the SabaAH [which means both dawn and forenoon]: 
so in the saying, laqiytuhu caAta SuboHapK [I met him when he was entering upon the dawn or forenoon]. (TA.)

entry.sense:
One says, bihimo tuvonaI AlOaSaAbiEu [With the mention of them the fingers are bent]; meaning that they are reckoned as the best, [or among the best,] 
for the best are not many. 
(M, on a verse cited in the first paragraph {1} 
of art. vnI.) 
[See also two similar exs. in the first paragraph {1} 
of art. Hnw and HnI.]

hom.sense:
Hence, in a trad., the saying of Umm-Selemeh to ʼÁïsheh, sak-ana Qll-ehu EuqayoraAki falaA tuSoHiriyhaA [app. meaning, accord. to explanations of it in the TA in art. Eqr, God hath made thy dwelling and estate, or, as Z explains it, thy person (nafosaki), to be quietly settled, therefore do not thou remove it forth to the desert]; i. e. laA tuboriziyhaA UilaI AlS-aHoraMCi; 


the verb, accord. to IAth, being made trans. by the suppression of the prep.; [i. e. tuSoHiriyhaA being for tuSoHiriI bihaA;] for it is [properly] intrans. 
(TA. [See also the next sentence but one, in which the verb is tropically made trans.])

entry.sense:
And SaHaA mino sukorihi, (Ṣ, Mṣb,) aor. yaSoHuw, (Mṣb,) inf. n. SaHowN (Ṣ, Mṣb, Ḳ) and SuHuw-N, (Mṣb,) [He recovered, or became free, from his intoxication; or] his intoxication ceased; 
as also ASHI↓: (Mṣb:) and SaHiIa, (Ḳ, TA,) inf. n. SaHFA; (TA;) 
as also ASHI↓; (IḲṭṭ, Ḳ, TA;) is [likewise] said of one intoxicated; (Ḳ, TA;) both meaning he recovered from his state of insensibility; (TA;) and in like manner both are said of one affected with desire, or yearning or longing in the soul; (Ḳ, TA;) [and also of one sleeping, meaning he awoke: 
see an ex. of the former of these two verbs in this last sense in the latter part of the second paragraph {2} 
of art. frT.]

muSoHK; 
