muSaAriEN One who wrestles with another, endeavouring to throw him down; 
as also SiroEN↓: you say, 
humaA SiroEaAni↓ i. e. They are two persons wrestling together, each endeavouring to throw down the other. (Ḳ,* TA.)

hom.sense:
Also † Decision, or determination, (Ṣ, M, Ḳ TA,) EalaI XaIoCK [to do a thing]: (Ṣ, TA:) and the deciding of an affair, (M, Ḳ, TA,) and the firm, or sound, execution thereof: (TA:) or an object of want upon accomplishment of which one has decided, or determined; 


as also EaziymapN: (AHeyth, TA:) pl. SaraAYimu. (TA.) 
One says, huwa maADi AlS-ariymapi and AlS-araAYimi [He is effective of decision, &c. and of decisions, &c.]. (TA.)

SaEowN 
A small EuSofuwr [or bird of the sparrowkind], (Ḳ, TA,) red in the head; (TA;) 
fem. with p {SaEowapN}: (Ḳ:) or small EaSaAfiyr [or birds of the sparrow-kind], the heads of which are red; 
n. un. with p: (Mṣb:) or SaEowapN signifies a certain bird; 
and its pl. is SaEowN and SiEaMCN: (Ṣ:) or the pl. (of SaEowapN, Mṣb) is SiEaMCN (Mṣb, Ḳ) and SaEawaAtN, (Ḳ, in the CK SEowAtN,) and 
the pl. of SaEowN is OaSoEaMCN: some say that SaEowN is originally waSoEN. (TA.)

entry.sense:
